reviewText: Among my favorites of the Power Ranger seasons I was so happy that Timeforce finally got a DVD release. Best of all its whole season without missing any episode like some of the Disney season releases got.  Having come before SPD its a little awkward comparing the two future view points if not for the fact that while  Time Force Rangers are in our time the future does get altered some as they try to round up all the escape mutants who they followed to 21st century.  About the only real flaw in the series is  a lack of motivation on the part of the rangers. They never ever tried once to location the villians headquarters just wanted for the mutants to come to them to round up. Also has some great Ranger team ups with Light Speed Rangers and the return of the villians from their series.
As good as this series is (and it is VERY good for  Power Rangers), there are too many filler episodes and an unnecessary clip show. I think Dino Thunder and SPD are better.
My son loves power rangers, and it is great all in one.  Takes up little space compared to all the hard box VHS we had.

Just an absolutely wonderful series!  I was absolutely wonderful to get to relive these characters and stories from 15 years ago.

Shout factory does a nice job with their DVDs (as usual.) Nothing but praise here.  I won't be getting anymore Power Ranger DVDs since I now own all the ones I like.

However, if you are a fan of the whole series, or knows someone that is, you can feel confident that you are getting terrific DVDs from the Shout Company.

What could I say that has not been said already....one of the best cast and most fleshed out villains in the series history. Hands down one of the best Pink Rangers of all time. The interplay between the characters really shows the depth in their relationships. Ransik has one of the best Story Arks since 'Green with Evil'. This is a must own set for any Power Rangers fan and my second favorite season of the show with RPM coming in first!

This is the complete series of Power Rangers Time Force. It features over 14 hours of Power Rangers adventures. My boys have always enjoyed Power Rangers and somehow I don't think we caught any of these episodes when they were on television. The show is set in the future and the Power Rangers fight futuristic bad guys. I like that it has a sci-fi feel to it but still for kids. Now it does have weapons and fighting in it, so if your not sure about it for your kids then definitely pre-watch it. My kids know that the show is not real and they know not to do what the characters do.

DON'T BUY THIS, get the sets that contain multiple seasons. If you do this, you can have the first 17 seasons made by Shout! Factory. http://www.amazon.com/Power-Rangers-Seasons-Eight-Twelve/dp/B00EALTVJ6 The sets are cheaper and contain more content.

One of the best and most popular seasons of Power Rangers. The story? Awesome. The acting? Best of the show. Action? Best of the Saban era. I remember watching these back in 2001 and it's just as good today as it was back then. A season certainly worth checking out.

Finally Power Rangers Time Force is being released individually in stores on DVD. Out of all the old seasons, I'd have to say that this is one of the best ever. The finale is just awesome. Cannot wait for it to come out on December 15th 2015! Note: If you are buying this for your kids and they are either under the age of 6 or are not used to seeing the good guys being badly beaten then you may want to introduce them to the finale of this Power Rangers series gradually so that it does not scare them. But other than that there is no reason that you shouldn't pick this one up because it is a really great season and you don't want to deprive the Power Rangers fan in your family something that is fun to watch.
